0Moradian%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles-based%20associate%20at%20Simpson%20Thacher%20%26amp%3B%20Bartlett%2C%20joined%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20his%20colleagues%2C%20Moradian%20criticized%20the%20firm's%20decision%20to%20make%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20White%20House%2C%20which%20included%20about%20%24125%20million%20in%20pro%20bono%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20capitulating%20today%2C%20Simpson%20Thacher%20joins%20several%20other%20historic%2C%20powerful%2C%20influential%2C%20and%20well-resourced%20law%20firms%20in%20bending%20the%20knee%20and%20kissing%20the%20ring%20of%20authoritarianism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIf%20even%20lawyers%20won't%20fight%20unlawful%20governmental%20weaponization%20of%20the%20courts%2C%20who%20will%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoradian%20then%20left%20his%20position%20at%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Moradian%20said%20he%20previously%20thought%20about%20leaving%20before%20Simpson%20Thacher%20made%20its%20deal%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20something%20that%20I%20was%20contemplating%20ever%20since%20Paul%20Weiss%20and%20Skadden%20capitulated%2C%20and%20I%20saw%20that%2C%20to%20my%20surprise%2C%20firms%20were%20a%20lot%20more%20willing%20to%20cut%20a%20deal%20than%20I%20thought%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20executive%20orders%20and%20the%20EEOC%20letters%20to%20the%20respective%20firms%20were%20sent%20out%2C%20I%20felt%20quite%20confident%20that%20these%20well-resourced%20law%20firms%20are%20not%20going%20to%20fold%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20going%20to%20fight%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20I%20saw%20that%20I%20was%2C%20I%20guess%2C%20misguided%20in%20that%20expectation%2C%20I%20had%20begun%20thinking%20what%20I%20would%20do%20if%20Simpson%20was%20put%20in%20that%20position%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoradian%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20a%20legal%20standpoint%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20an%20easy%20fight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20what%20becomes%20really%20concerning%20for%20me%20is%20that%20these%20law%20firms%20are%20not%20making%20deals%20because%20of%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20claims%20or%20potential%20claims%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20extra-legal%20extortionist%20tactics%2C%20and%20it%20just%20seems%20like%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%20and%20something%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20going%20to%20add%20to%20their%20playbook%20of%20weaponizing%20the%20legal%20system%20in%20the%20courts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoradian%20joins%20former%20Skadden%20associates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frachel-cohen-harvard-lawyer-quit-big-law-trump-legal-fights-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERachel%20Cohen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskadden-deal-donald-trump-big-law-firm-unforgivable-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrenna%20Frey%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20who%20also%20resigned%20over%20their%20firm's%20deal%20with%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20now%20secured%20about%20%24940%20million%20in%20pro%20bono%20legal%20work%20from%20a%20range%20of%20firms%2C%20including%20Simpson%20Thacher%2C%20Skadden%2C%20Willkie%20Farr%20%26amp%3B%20Gallagher%2C%20Milbank%20LLP%2C%20and%20Paul%20Weiss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20firms%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20fought%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenner%20%26amp%3B%20Block%2C%20Perkins%20Coie%2C%20and%20WilmerHale%20have%20all%20sued%20the%20administration%20over%20the%20executive%20orders.%20And%20this%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-susman-godfrey-executive-order-dominion-big-law-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESusman%20Godfrey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20target%20of%20a%20similar%20executive%20order%2